	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "kernel: watchdog: Fix possible use-after-free by calling del_timer_sync() (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2021-47321",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2021-47321",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A vulnerability was found  in the del_timer() function in the Linux kernel's watchdog driver. This issue occurs because the function does not wait for the timer handler to finish, which may lead to a situation where the handler runs after the driver that has been removed, causing a use-after-free issue. \n            STATEMENT: This vulnerability is rated as a moderate severity because this issue does not allow unauthorized access or data leakage, but it poses a risk of system instability and crashes. The potential for a use-after-free condition can disrupt normal operations.\n            MITIGATION: Red Hat has investigated whether a possible mitigation exists for this issue, and has not been able to identify a practical example. Please update the affected package as soon as possible.",
